            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01PyAUk4KX4yqECcN8SkMXME\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I appreciate the detail, but I need to redirect here—you've just described part of your *solution* (the vetting process), not your *audience*.\\n\\nLet me ask more directly: **Who are the podcast hosts you're targeting?** Are they:\\n- Solo indie creators just starting out?\\n- Established shows with 50k+ listeners?\\n- B2B/niche podcasts in specific industries?\\n- A mix?\\n\\nAnd what's their main goal—grow their audience, save time, improve content quality, or something else?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Who is your ideal podcast host customer? What size/stage are they at, and what's their primary motivation for using Friend of the Pod?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Mid-sized shows (10k-100k listeners) that want to grow but are drowning in guest outreach\\\",\\n    \\\"Niche B2B podcasts where finding credible experts in their space is nearly impossible\\\",\\n    \\\"Busy hosts who just want to outsource the entire guest-finding headache\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2705,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":253,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
