            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Help me answer this question\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n  The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n      We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n</background>\\n\\n<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n      business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<context>\\n  The user has clicked \\\"help me answer\\\" on a specific question because they need more guidance on how to respond. They are not asking you to answer FOR them, but to help them structure their own thinking.\\n</context>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n</role>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Provide a clear, fill-in-the-blank template that helps them articulate their answer with specificity and clarity.\\n</task>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  1. **Brief acknowledgment** (1 sentence max)\\n\\n              - Encouraging and supportive\\n              - Examples: \\\"No problem! Let me help you structure this.\\\" or \\\"Sure! Let me break this down for you.\\\"\\n\\n              2. **Structured template or framework**\\n\\n              - Provide clear fill-in-the-blank placeholders using [brackets]\\n              - OR break the question into 3-4 sub-questions with placeholders\\n              - Include brief guidance for what should go in each placeholder\\n              - Keep explanatory text minimal - let the structure do the work\\n\\n              3. **Concrete, realistic example** (REQUIRED)\\n              - Must demonstrate the template/framework filled out completely\\n              - Should be realistic and relatable, not overly creative or niche\\n              - Must show how all pieces connect together\\n</output_format_rules>\\nTONE REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n          - Helpful and encouraging, never condescending\\n          - Conversational but professional\\n          - Like a business coach or advisor, not a teacher\\n          - Assume they're smart but just need structure\\n\\n          CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:\\n\\n          - Keep your response under 200 words total (before the example)\\n          - Use simple, jargon-free language - no marketing or business buzzwords\\n          - Do NOT ask follow-up questions\\n          - Do NOT offer to help further or ask if they need clarification\\n          - Do NOT answer the question for them or guess at their answer\\n          - The template/structure should be immediately usable\\n          - Focus entirely on STRUCTURE, not on generating ideas for them\\n\\n          OUTPUT FORMAT:\\n          Your response will be displayed in a chat interface and the template portion may be pre-filled into an input box for them to edit. Make sure the template is clearly delineated from your explanation.\\n\\n          QUALITY SELF-CHECK:\\n          Before providing your response, verify:\\n          ✓ Is there a clear template or framework they can fill in?\\n          ✓ Does my example show the template properly filled out?\\n          ✓ Does my example use any information we've already collected to help think through the answer for THEIR business?\\n          ✓ Can someone with no business background follow this?\\n          ✓ Is this MORE helpful than just rephrasing the original question?\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  audience: The target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\n\\nsolution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\n\\nsocialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  audience\\n</current_topic>\\nTOPIC: Target Audience\\n\\nThe user needs help describing who their ideal customer is and what problems they face.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- Break this into 3-4 clear sub-questions\\n- Sub-questions should build logically: WHO → PROBLEMS → GOALS → (optionally) WHY EXISTING SOLUTIONS FAIL\\n- Each sub-question should have a bold header and bracketed guidance\\n- Help them get specific about demographics AND psychographics\\n- Emphasize connecting problems to goals (they're two sides of same coin)\\n\\nSUB-QUESTIONS TO INCLUDE:\\n\\n1. **Who are they?** - Demographics, role, life context\\n2. **What problems do they face?** - Pain points, frustrations, obstacles\\n3. **What are they trying to achieve?** - Goals, desired outcomes, aspirations\\n4. (Optional) **Why don't current solutions work?** - Gap in market\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Should paint a vivid picture of a real person\\n- Must show clear connection between their problems and goals\\n- Problems should be specific, not generic (\\\"overwhelmed by too much to do\\\")\\n- Should help them see the emotional dimension, not just functional\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"Busy professionals who want to save time\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"Marketing managers at 10-50 person SaaS companies who are stretched thin managing multiple channels, feel guilty about inconsistent posting, and want to build thought leadership but can't justify hiring a full-time content person.\\\"\\n<task>\\n  Provide a clear, fill-in-the-blank template that helps them articulate their answer with specificity and clarity.\\n</task>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in this exact format:\\n\\n              {\\n                \\\"type\\\": \\\"helpMe\\\",\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief acknowledgement\\\",\\n                \\\"template\\\": \\\"Structured template or framework\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"],\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in this format.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"helpMe\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Acknowledge the user and explain that you will help them structure their answer\\\"},\\\"template\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"REQUIRED: A structured template or framework to help the user articulate their answer with specificity and clarity\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: A concrete, realistic example to help the user understand\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\",\\\"template\\\",\\\"examples\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2594,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2594,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01RY6VM892SwTWPtYLV4tVVc\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"helpMe\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Perfect! Let me help you get specific about who you're selling to and what keeps them up at night.\\\",\\n  \\\"template\\\": \\\"**1. Who are they?**\\\\n[Job title/role] at [company size/type] who [specific context about their work]\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main pain point?**\\\\nThey spend [time/effort] on [specific task], which makes them feel [emotion], and it [concrete consequence]\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they actually trying to achieve?**\\\\nThey want to [specific goal] so they can [bigger outcome]\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why doesn't what they're doing now work?**\\\\n[Current approach] fails because [specific reason]\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Podcast hosts with 5K-50K listeners who are actively growing their show\\\\n\\\\n**2. Pain point:** They spend 8-10 hours per week hunting for guests on LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, which feels like a waste of time and makes them frustrated because they could be editing or promoting instead. It also means they often settle for mediocre guests just to fill slots.\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want to book high-quality, relevant guests consistently so their show stays fresh, their audience stays engaged, and they can focus on production instead of sourcing.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why current approach fails:** Manual searching is slow, hit-or-miss, and doesn't scale. Guest databases are outdated. Asking their network gets repetitive. There's no systematic way to find the *right* person fast.\\\",\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Independent creators and thought leaders who want podcast exposure but don't have a booking agent\\\\n\\\\n**2. Pain point:** They get maybe 1-2 podcast invitations per month through random outreach, which feels like they're invisible despite having valuable expertise. It's frustrating because they know their message could reach more people.\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want to appear on 2-3 relevant podcasts per month so they can build authority, reach new audiences, and create content they can repurpose.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why current approach fails:** There's no easy way to get discovered by hosts. Pitching cold is ineffective. Most platforms focus on the host side, not the guest side.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2807,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":549,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
