          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1573,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_019DU8YCLcQvwouiYyYNLAXV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I appreciate the enthusiasm, but let's stay focused! 😄\\n\\nYou just told me about **Friend of the Pod**—a podcast matchmaking service. That's a real business idea with potential. Now I need you to help me understand what makes it special.\\n\\nHere's what I need from you:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's nail down your core idea. You mentioned Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service, but I need clarity on the specifics. What exactly are you matching? Who are the two sides of this marketplace? And what's the problem you're solving that existing podcast platforms aren't?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"We match podcast hosts with guest experts in their niche—hosts save time finding credible guests, experts get exposure to relevant audiences\\\",\\n    \\\"We connect podcasters looking for co-hosts with compatible partners based on style, audience size, and content focus\\\",\\n    \\\"We match listeners to podcasts they'll actually love by analyzing their interests deeper than algorithm-based discovery\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Give me a clear answer: Who are you connecting, and why does your way work better?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2561,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":265,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
